Marian Robinson, the mother of former first lady Michelle Obama, has died, according to a statement from the Obama and Robinson families. She was 86. Even in the rain, kids grabbed their poles and participated in a local fishing tournament at Noble Park on Saturday. The McCracken County Special Olympics Track Team is traveling to Richmond, Kentucky, for the State Summer Games. The team set out from Reidland Middle School Friday morning. The Marshall County Fiscal Court will hold a meeting at 9 a.m., Tuesday, June 4, in the Fiscal Court Room. "Donald Trump is not above the law and suggesting that Trump’s charges are political persecution is dangerous rhetoric," the Democratic Party of Illinois said in a statement. Construction projects by Canadian National Railway will necessitate the closure of Grand Avenue from Monday, June 3, to Friday, June 7, between Illinois Avenue and Washington Street. The City of Carbondale Police Department has investigated several reports of thefts and attempted thefts of Kias, Hyundais and Dodges — particularly Dodge Challengers — during the month of May, the department reported Friday. Downtown Paducah event Cars and Cigars will return at 5 p.m. Saturday, June 15, organizers announced Friday. Local nonprofit library aid organization Friends of the Marion Carnegie Library will host a community book sale from 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. Friday, May 31; and Saturday, June 1, at Marion Carnegie Library. That\'s the highest in 45 years of records. More than two dozen doctors, public health experts, meteorologists and other experts tell The AP the real death toll was higher. Coroner, hospital, ambulance and weather records show that last summer amped up America’s heat and health problem to a new level. The relentless warmth unusually killed more people in the South, which had been less prone to mass deaths. Are you a golfer looking for some play time?
